\cf0 Part of acceptance means giving up on the idea of perfection. What are some ways that you irrationally hold on to the idea of perfection. How could you reframe your thoughts to accept the idea that nothing is perfect?\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Give up the idea of having zero contradictions, and the pride I take in it.\
Give up \'91my way is the right way\'92.\
Give up most efficient being the best.\
Let go of my \'93Family advice is always right\'94.\
Let kids understand that there are plenty of times yet to do better or be perfect. \
Treat perfection as being a moment in time and seek out other moments that may have passed me by.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
Think about an incident from your past that you are holding on to. What makes it hard to let go? What would happen if you looked at it rationally? Use the space below to work out the situation dispassionately as if it happened to someone else. Consider whether or not you can accept this incident as something that happened in the past and move on from it.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Betrayed by friend who was drug addict.\
Hard to let go because it impacted another friend who was innocent, ruined my reputation with that friend and whole friend group. Felt heartbroken and worthless when sold out for a few thousand dollars.\
Rationally the person was afflicted with cravings that sold me out for the next hit. It was not personal from their side.\
My innocent friend & wider group moved on against me, my reputation is just my perception of what people think. I can control that.\
This has passed and I can move on.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
